'''Adolf Bötticher''' or '''Adolf Boetticher''' (12 December 1842 &ndash; 9 June 1901) was a [[Germany|German]] [[art history|art historian]] and [[Conservator (museum)|conservator]].
Bötticher was born in [[Ahrensfelde|Blumberg]], [[Province of Brandenburg|Brandenburg]], and studied at the [[Bauakademie]] in [[Berlin]] (1865–68). After performing excavatory work in [[Greece]] from 1875–77, he published a weekly newspaper for architects and engineers (''Wochenblatt für Architekten und Ingenieure''). In 1886 Bötticher headed the registry for historic buildings and art monuments in [[East Prussia]], and in 1891 he was named conservator for the province.<ref>[https://www.deutsche-biographie.de/pnd116226420.html#ndbcontent Bötticher, Adolf] at [[Neue Deutsche Biographie]]</ref> He died in [[Lesnoye, Zelenogradsk, Kaliningrad Oblast|Warnicken]]. [[File:"Pelasgische" Mauer - Boetticher Adolf - 1888.jpg|right|thumb|[[Pelasgic wall]], illustration from ''Die Akropolis von Athen'' (1888).]]
== Published works == From 1891–98 he published the 8-volume [https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/010249794 ''Die Bau und Kunstdenkmäler der Provinz Ostpreussen''] (9th volume, 1899 by Walther von Schimmelfennig),<ref>[https://de.wikisource.org/wiki/Kunstdenkm%C3%A4ler Kunstdenkmäler] de.Wikisource</ref> documenting architectural and artistic landmarks of East Prussia. Other noted works by Bötticher include: * ''Auf griechischen Landstrassen'', 1883 &ndash; On Greek country roads. * ''Olympia, das fest und seine stätte, nach den berichten der alten und den ergebnissen der deutschen augrabungen'', 1886 &ndash; [[Olympia, Greece|Olympia]], the festival and its site, according to old records and the results of German excavations. * ''Die Akropolis von Athen nach den berichten der alten und den neusten erforschungen'', 1888<ref>{{cite journal|title=Review of ''Mythology and Monuments of Ancient Athens'' by Jane E. Harrison and Margaret de G. Verrall; ''Die Akropolis von Athen'' von Adolf Bötticher|journal=The Quarterly Journal|volume=171|date=July 1890|pages=122–149|url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=hvd.32044092526573;view=1up;seq=136}}</ref> &ndash; The [[Acropolis]] of Athens, according to old reports and the latest research.<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n86-055189/ Most widely held works by Adolf Boetticher] WorldCat Identities</ref>
==References== *{{cite book|last=Albinus|first=Robert|authorlink=|title=Lexikon der Stadt Königsberg Pr. und Umgebung|year=1985|publisher=Verlag Gerhard Rautenberg|location=Leer|pages=371|isbn=3-7921-0320-6|language=de}} {{reflist}}
