[[File:Roger Gaillard.JPG|thumb|Roger Gaillard at his residence in [[Kenscoff]] of 1973.]]
'''Roger Gaillard''' (10 April 1923 &ndash; 2000) was a [[Haiti]]an historian and novelist. Born in [[Port-au-Prince]], Gaillard earned a philosophy degree at the [[University of Paris]] in France. He is best known for his multiple-volume chronicle of the [[United States occupation of Haiti (1915-1934)|United States' occupation of Haiti]].
==Selected works== * ''L'Univers Romanesque de [[Jacques Roumain]]'' (1965) * ''La Destinée de [[Carl Brouard]]'' (1966) * ''Les Cent Jours de [[Rosalvo Bobo]]'' (1973) * ''[[Charlemagne Péralte]] le Caco'' (1982) * ''La Guérilla de Batraville'' (1983) * ''La Déroute de l'Intelligence'' (1992)
